' mid
' ---

' 'mid(s, n)' returns the character at index n in the string s (0 is the index of the first
' character).
pln "mid(" + chr(34) + "ectoplasm" + chr(34) + ", 4) = " + mid("ectoplasm", 4)

' 'mid(s, n, m)' returns m characters, starting at character index n, of the string s.
pln "mid(" + chr(34) + "ectoplasm" + chr(34) + ", 2, 3) = " + mid("ectoplasm", 2, 3)

system "pause"
